  <compounddef id="CURSOR" kind="page">
    <compoundname>CURSOR</compoundname>
    <title>CURSOR Keyword</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">CURSOR<sp/>integer-expression,<sp/>integer-expression</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Moves the <bold>text cursor</bold> to the given <computeroutput>X,Y</computeroutput> coordinates (column, row). <linebreak/>
 The origin is the <bold>top-left corner</bold> at <computeroutput>(0,0)</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>X</computeroutput> = column (0 is the leftmost column)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>Y</computeroutput> = row (0 is the top row)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>After moving the cursor, subsequent <ref refid="PRINT" kindref="compound">PRINT</ref> output starts at that position.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><heading level="5">Example</heading>
</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">CLS</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">CURSOR<sp/>10,<sp/>5</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Hello<sp/>from<sp/>(10,5)&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Use <ref refid="TERMWIDTH" kindref="compound">TERMWIDTH</ref> and </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para><ref refid="TERMHEIGHT" kindref="compound">TERMHEIGHT</ref> to compute </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>safe positions or to centre text.</para>
</simplesect>
<hruler/>
</para>
<para><heading level="5">Notes</heading>
</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Affects the <bold>text layer</bold> only; graphics primitives (e.g. <ref refid="LINE" kindref="compound">LINE</ref>) are unaffected.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The cursor is reset to <computeroutput>(0,0)</computeroutput> by <ref refid="CLS" kindref="compound">CLS</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Valid screen coordinates depend on the current terminal size (<computeroutput>0..TERMWIDTH-1</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>0..TERMHEIGHT-1</computeroutput>). </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
